# 🔹 Basic Operations

---

## 1️⃣ Push

Insert element into stack.

Example:

```text
Before:
10 20

Push 30

After:
10 20 30
```

Time Complexity:

[
O(1)
]

---

## 2️⃣ Pop

Remove top element.

```text
10 20 30

Pop

10 20
```

Time Complexity:

[
O(1)
]

---

## 3️⃣ Peek / Top

Returns top element.

Time Complexity:

[
O(1)
]

---

## 4️⃣ isEmpty()

Checks whether stack is empty.

---

## 5️⃣ isFull()

Checks overflow condition (array implementation).

---

# 🔹 Stack Implementation Using Array

---

### Declaration

```c
int stack[100];
int top = -1;
```

---

### Push

```c
top++;
stack[top] = value;
```

---

### Pop

```c
value = stack[top];
top--;
```

---

### Conditions

Overflow:

```c
top == MAX-1
```

Underflow:

```c
top == -1
```

📌 Frequently asked in GATE.

---

# 🔹 Stack Implementation Using Linked List

Structure:

```c
struct Node
{
    int data;
    struct Node *next;
};
```

Top points to first node.

---

## Advantages

✅ Dynamic size

✅ No overflow until memory available

---

## Disadvantages

❌ Extra pointer memory

